# Local-dev environment for the kedge "agents" provider.
#
# Copy to providers/agents/.env only when you need to override defaults.
# `make run-provider-agents` and both Tiltfiles auto-source the gitignored
# .env file, so no manual `export` is needed.
#
# By default, local dev starts a Postgres container named
# kedge-agents-postgres (see AGENTS_DEV_DATABASE_URL in the Makefile) and
# points the provider at it, so agents, sessions, memory, schedules, and
# audit survive provider restarts and hard refreshes.
#
# NOTE: LLM/model credentials are NOT configured here. Each agent references a
# named model credential you create in the portal (Models → New), stored as a
# per-credential Secret. There is no single provider-wide API key env var.
#
# ── Store ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Use an existing Postgres instead of the local dev container.
# AGENTS_DATABASE_URL=postgres://agents:agents@localhost:55434/agents?sslmode=disable
#
# Force the old non-durable in-memory store for one-off UI work.
# AGENTS_IN_MEMORY_STORE=true
#
# Optional at-rest message encryption key set.
# AGENTS_MESSAGE_ENCRYPTION_KEYS=primary:<base64-32-byte-aes-key>
#
# ── Background executor ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Signing key for trigger + channel inbound webhook URLs. Empty → derived from
# the provider kubeconfig contents. Set a stable value for multi-replica.
# AGENTS_WEBHOOK_KEY=dev-agents-webhook-secret
#
# Background poll cadence for autonomous schedules (default 30s).
# AGENTS_SCHEDULER_INTERVAL=30s
#
# ── Platform OAuth apps (optional) ───────────────────────────────────────────
# Configure an OAuth app once here and users click "Connect" on a matching
# connection with no client id/secret to paste (mirrors the code provider). If
# a provider is not set below, users bring their own OAuth app per connection.
#
# GitHub OAuth App (Settings → Developer settings → OAuth Apps). The callback
# URL must be <portal-origin>/services/providers/agents/oauth/callback.
# AGENTS_GITHUB_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=
# AGENTS_GITHUB_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET=
#
# Google OAuth client (offline access is requested automatically).
# AGENTS_GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=
# AGENTS_GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET=
#
# Slack OAuth app (oauth.v2.access).
# AGENTS_SLACK_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=
# AGENTS_SLACK_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET=
